Lets explore some of the key components of the Tint2 panel at the bottom of the screen.

(1) Application Finder (Application Menu)

(2) Settings Manager
(3) Thunar File Manager
(4) Web Browser

(5) Notification Area consisting of:
    • Update manager
    • Clipboard manager
    • Network manager
    • Sound manager

(6) Clock (Date Time)
    • Left-Click to open a calendar, Escape (Esc) to close
    • Right-Click to set a alarm
    
(7) Power Button which opens a window to:
    • Lock • Log Out • Restart • Shutdown • Suspend

Panel location and orientation is easily changeable in MX Tools > MX Tweak.

Even more options to customize your panel exist under Settings Manager > Tint2 Manager
